<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1545,2038]" pageId="1" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,296,1545,1570]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="389" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[306,439,1545,1569]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="389">Adult male.</emphasis>
Length of each forewing 4.0–5.0 mm (n = 101). Color, in alcohol, brown. Head dark brown with dark brown setae; antennae dark brown, covered by short brown setae. Forewings dark brown, with median transversal white bar; wing venation typical for the subgenus. Legs yellowish brown. Sternum V with pair of anterolateral glandular processes of same length as sternum. Abdomen internally with two pairs of reticulate glandular structures, associated with posterolateral margins of segments VI and VII.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1545,2038]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,1221]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="390" pageId="1" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis box="[199,375,1725,1749]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="389">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Segment IX, in dorsal view, with anterodorsal margin concave, median membranous area covered with small spicules, lateral margins sinuous (
<figureCitation box="[754,845,1761,1786]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1946,1968]" captionTargetBox="[212,1377,194,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-79@4.[212,1378,193,1925]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Smicridea (Smicridea) caatinga sp. nov., holotype male. 2A, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, dorsal. 2B, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, right lateral. 2C–2E, retracted phallus: 2C, right lateral; 2D, dorsal; 2E, ventral. 2F– 2G, everted phallus: 2F, right lateral; 2G, posterior or caudal. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297735/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="389">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); in lateral view with anterolateral margins rounded, ventral margin 1/4 as long as dorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[692,785,1797,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1946,1968]" captionTargetBox="[212,1377,194,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-79@4.[212,1378,193,1925]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Smicridea (Smicridea) caatinga sp. nov., holotype male. 2A, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, dorsal. 2B, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, right lateral. 2C–2E, retracted phallus: 2C, right lateral; 2D, dorsal; 2E, ventral. 2F– 2G, everted phallus: 2F, right lateral; 2G, posterior or caudal. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297735/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="389">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Segment X short, covered with short setae on lateral margins; in dorsal view, medially divided into pair of lobes, each divided apically into rectilinear mesal angle and round lateral lobe (
<figureCitation box="[378,474,1869,1894]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1946,1968]" captionTargetBox="[212,1377,194,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-79@4.[212,1378,193,1925]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Smicridea (Smicridea) caatinga sp. nov., holotype male. 2A, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, dorsal. 2B, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, right lateral. 2C–2E, retracted phallus: 2C, right lateral; 2D, dorsal; 2E, ventral. 2F– 2G, everted phallus: 2F, right lateral; 2G, posterior or caudal. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297735/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="389">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); in lateral view, apex rounded and upturned (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1120,1869,1894]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1946,1968]" captionTargetBox="[212,1377,194,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-79@4.[212,1378,193,1925]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Smicridea (Smicridea) caatinga sp. nov., holotype male. 2A, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, dorsal. 2B, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, right lateral. 2C–2E, retracted phallus: 2C, right lateral; 2D, dorsal; 2E, ventral. 2F– 2G, everted phallus: 2F, right lateral; 2G, posterior or caudal. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297735/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="389">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Inferior appendages twosegmented; each with first article long, slightly inflated distally, setose, with long, fine apical setae (
<figureCitation box="[1275,1423,1905,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1946,1968]" captionTargetBox="[212,1377,194,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-79@4.[212,1378,193,1925]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Smicridea (Smicridea) caatinga sp. nov., holotype male. 2A, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, dorsal. 2B, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, right lateral. 2C–2E, retracted phallus: 2C, right lateral; 2D, dorsal; 2E, ventral. 2F– 2G, everted phallus: 2F, right lateral; 2G, posterior or caudal. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297735/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="389">Figs. 2A–2B</figureCitation>
); second article short, about 1/2 as long as first article, setose, with dorsal tuft of setae subapically, in dorsal view slightly curved mesad, slightly inflated on distal half with acute apex (
<figureCitation box="[950,1041,1977,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1946,1968]" captionTargetBox="[212,1377,194,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-79@4.[212,1378,193,1925]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Smicridea (Smicridea) caatinga sp. nov., holotype male. 2A, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, dorsal. 2B, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, right lateral. 2C–2E, retracted phallus: 2C, right lateral; 2D, dorsal; 2E, ventral. 2F– 2G, everted phallus: 2F, right lateral; 2G, posterior or caudal. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297735/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="389">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); in lateral view, clavate (
<figureCitation box="[1334,1423,1977,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1946,1968]" captionTargetBox="[212,1377,194,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-79@4.[212,1378,193,1925]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Smicridea (Smicridea) caatinga sp. nov., holotype male. 2A, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, dorsal. 2B, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, right lateral. 2C–2E, retracted phallus: 2C, right lateral; 2D, dorsal; 2E, ventral. 2F– 2G, everted phallus: 2F, right lateral; 2G, posterior or caudal. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297735/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="389">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Phallus short and complex, enlarged basally, open apically, without basal curvature, with apex quadrangular and pair of dorsal mesolateral lobes covered by short setae, and with pair of ventrolateral sclerotized projections directed apicolaterad (
<figureCitation box="[410,560,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1946,1968]" captionTargetBox="[212,1377,194,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-79@4.[212,1378,193,1925]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Smicridea (Smicridea) caatinga sp. nov., holotype male. 2A, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, dorsal. 2B, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, right lateral. 2C–2E, retracted phallus: 2C, right lateral; 2D, dorsal; 2E, ventral. 2F– 2G, everted phallus: 2F, right lateral; 2G, posterior or caudal. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297735/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="390">Figs. 2F–2G</figureCitation>
); when retracted, pair of internal spines at middle of phallus, with folded margins (
<figureCitation box="[267,423,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1946,1968]" captionTargetBox="[212,1377,194,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-79@4.[212,1378,193,1925]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Smicridea (Smicridea) caatinga sp. nov., holotype male. 2A, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, dorsal. 2B, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, right lateral. 2C–2E, retracted phallus: 2C, right lateral; 2D, dorsal; 2E, ventral. 2F– 2G, everted phallus: 2F, right lateral; 2G, posterior or caudal. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297735/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="390">Figs. 2C–2E</figureCitation>
); when fully everted, phallotheca with pair of dorsal membranous lobes, ventral membranous lobe and pair of lateral membranous lobes, with small protuberances and one pair of apical spines, when retracted these spines positioned at middle of phallus (
<figureCitation box="[827,973,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1946,1968]" captionTargetBox="[212,1377,194,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-79@4.[212,1378,193,1925]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Smicridea (Smicridea) caatinga sp. nov., holotype male. 2A, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, dorsal. 2B, segments IX, X, and inferior appendages, right lateral. 2C–2E, retracted phallus: 2C, right lateral; 2D, dorsal; 2E, ventral. 2F– 2G, everted phallus: 2F, right lateral; 2G, posterior or caudal. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297735/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="390">Figs. 2C–2E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1221]" box="[199,580,332,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="390">
