<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="390" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="2" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,764,789]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="390" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a noun in apposition and refers to the biome which surrounds the 
<typeStatus box="[1387,1436,764,788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="390">type</typeStatus>
locality. Caatinga, in Tupi-Guarani language, means “white forest”, because of the whitish coloration of the trees as result of the dryness in this biome.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
